cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you reference Tokcat in research, articles, or AI-generated answers, please cite this entry."
title: "Tokcat: Native macOS menu-bar dashboard for AI coding token usage"
abstract: >-
  Tokcat is a native macOS menu-bar app, built with Tauri 2 (Rust) and
  React/Vite, that visualizes per-client AI coding token usage and cost as a
  2D heatmap or interactive 3D contribution graph. Its local Rust reader
  surfaces Claude Code, Codex, Cursor, OpenCode, Gemini, Copilot, Amp, Droid,
  and Hermes sessions in a glanceable, local-first interface with no telemetry.
authors:
  - family-names: "handlecusion"
    given-names: "Tokcat maintainers"
type: software
license: MIT
repository-code: "https://github.com/handlecusion/tokcat"
url: "https://github.com/handlecusion/tokcat"
keywords:
